inventory.description: Enjoy the Pacific sea breeze on a 45-minute sightseeing cruise around one of the largest port's in the world, the Port of LA. Board the vessel and look for California sea lions and admire landmarks, such as the USS Iowa, in one of the most active ports in the world. Listen to narration provided by the captain while you pass by the shoreline, container ships, massive cranes and more.Your cruise starts when you board a sightseeing boat at the historic San Pedro Ports O'Call near the lively fish market. During the 45-minute tour around the second-busiest container port in the US, you will see the container ships and other ocean vessels from all corners of the globe that bring in cargo such as bananas from Ecuador, perfume from France and electronics from Japan.Search for California sea lions and seals in their natural habitat, as you glide past the shoreline. While you cruise, your captain provides informative commentary, such as historical trivia about the USS Iowa, a retired battleship built in 1940.Other sights include state-of-the-art ship terminals, tall gantry cranes, the Vincent Thomas Bridge, Terminal Island and more.
